hopobject.body: I'm doing a phd in chemistry praventac indonesia The fact that the extinction event allowed these creatures to diversify gave them the chance to survive far into the future. During the Triassic, the cynodonts split into two groups--cynognathians and probainognathians. The first were mainly plant-eaters while the second were mainly flesh-eaters. These two groups seemed to rise and fall at random, but also gave rise to the first mammals about 25 million years after the mass extinction.
